<div id="linux-management" v-cloak>
  <div purpose="landing-page-container">
    <div purpose="landing-page-content">
      <div purpose="landing-page-hero">
        <div purpose="page-hero-content">
          <div purpose="page-hero-headings">
            <h4>Linux MDM</h4>
            <h1>Open source Linux MDM and device management</h1>
          </div>
          <div purpose="page-hero-text">
            <p>Support developers’ choice of Linux without losing visibility or control. <br>Manage Linux, macOS, and Windows in one place.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="button-row" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center">
            <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/whitepapers/it-leaders-guide-to-linux-device-management">Read the whitepaper</a>
            <animated-arrow-button href="/gitops-workshop">Join a workshop</animated-arrow-button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div><%/* landing-page-hero */%>
      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="intro-definition">
          <p><strong>Linux MDM</strong>, sometimes called Linux device management, is software that manages Linux desktops, laptops, and servers at scale. It covers patching, configuration, software inventory, compliance reporting, and remote scripting across distributions. Fleet is the open source platform for managing Linux alongside macOS, Windows, iOS, iPadOS, Android, and ChromeOS in one console.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>Linux devices create blind spots for IT</h3>
          <p>Linux is popular with developers and engineers. Most device management tools weren’t built for it. That gap creates risk.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="four-column-feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Distribution sprawl</h5>
            <p>Different package managers and update paths across distributions.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Inconsistent patching</h5>
            <p>Without automation, updates vary by device and by team.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Limited visibility</h5>
            <p>IT can’t easily see what’s installed or how devices are configured.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Fragmented workflows</h5>
            <p>Linux often sits outside your macOS and Windows management process.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image">
          <div purpose="feature-image">
            <img alt="A screenshot of Fleet showing scripts that can be run on a Linux device." src="/images/linux-management-feature-image-scripts-504x378@2x.png">
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-text">
            <h3>Manage Linux with the same visibility and control as other devices</h3>
            <p>Use Fleet to manage Linux devices at scale. Apply the same workflows you use for macOS and Windows.</p>
            <div purpose="checklist">
              <p>Run scripts remotely to automate installs, updates, and configuration</p>
              <p>Manage software across Debian-based and RPM-based distributions</p>
              <p>Monitor hardware, software, and compliance in real time</p>
              <p>Enforce security policies and track vulnerabilities across your fleet</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-quote">
          <div purpose="quote-image">
            <img alt="Nutanix logo" src="/images/logo-nutanix-140x32@2x.png">
          </div>
          <p purpose="quote-text">"We chose Fleet because they take Linux desktop management seriously. It was smooth as butter to set up and start deploying. Fleet gives me the peace of mind knowing that our Linux Fleet is properly managed, monitored, and secure."</p>
          <div purpose="quote-author-info">
            <div purpose="quote-author-image">
              <img alt="Roger Cantrell" src="/images/testimonial-author-roger-cantrell-100x100@2x.png">
            </div>
            <div purpose="name-and-title">
              <p purpose="author-name">Roger Cantrell</p>
              <p purpose="author-title">IT Operations Engineer</p>
              <p purpose="author-title">Nutanix</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h2>Built for Linux-first teams</h2>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Open source foundation</h5>
            <p>Fleet is open source. Review how devices are managed and adapt them to your needs.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>GitOps workflows</h5>
            <p>Version-control configuration. Propose changes with pull requests.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Unified device view</h5>
            <p>See Linux, macOS, and Windows devices in one interface.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Software inventory</h5>
            <p>Know exactly what’s installed across all distributions.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Policy enforcement</h5>
            <p>Define queries and policies to monitor compliance.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Works across environments</h5>
            <p>Manage cloud, on-prem, and mixed fleets with the same tools.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h2>Linux distributions Fleet manages</h2>
          <p>Manage Debian-based and RPM-based distributions side by side. Monitor any Linux device running osquery.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="distro-groups">
          <div purpose="distro-group">
            <h5>Debian-based</h5>
            <p purpose="distro-format">.deb packages</p>
            <ul purpose="distro-list">
              <li>Ubuntu</li>
              <li>Debian</li>
              <li>Linux Mint</li>
              <li>Pop!_OS</li>
              <li>Kali Linux</li>
              <li>KDE Neon</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div purpose="distro-group">
            <h5>RPM-based</h5>
            <p purpose="distro-format">.rpm packages</p>
            <ul purpose="distro-list">
              <li>Red Hat Enterprise Linux</li>
              <li>Fedora</li>
              <li>CentOS</li>
              <li>Amazon Linux</li>
              <li>openSUSE Leap</li>
              <li>openSUSE Tumbleweed</li>
              <li>SUSE Linux Enterprise</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div purpose="distro-group">
            <h5>Other distributions</h5>
            <p purpose="distro-format">Reporting and scripting</p>
            <ul purpose="distro-list">
              <li>Arch Linux</li>
              <li>Manjaro</li>
              <li>NixOS</li>
              <li>Gentoo</li>
              <li>Void Linux</li>
              <li>Flatcar</li>
              <li>CoreOS</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h4>How Fleet compares</h4>
          <h2>Fleet vs. other tools used to manage Linux</h2>
          <p>How Fleet stacks up against tools that IT and platform teams commonly use to manage Linux devices.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="comparison-table-section">
          <div purpose="table-legend">
            <div>
              <img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">
              Full support
            </div>
            <div>
              <span purpose="tilde">~</span>
              Limited
            </div>
            <div>
              <img alt="❌" purpose="red-x" src="/images/icon-emoji-x-12x12@2x.png">
              No support
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="comparison-table">
            <table>
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Capability</th>
                  <th>Fleet</th>
                  <th>Microsoft Intune</th>
                  <th>Ansible / Puppet</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>Built for endpoint device management</td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">Yes</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><span purpose="tilde">~</span>Linux is a secondary platform</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="❌" purpose="red-x" src="/images/icon-emoji-x-12x12@2x.png">Built for server configuration</div></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Broad Linux distribution support</td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">Debian, RPM, and beyond</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><span purpose="tilde">~</span>Limited to specific Ubuntu and RHEL versions</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">Any distro reachable over SSH</div></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Real-time inventory powered by osquery</td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">Live data on every host</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><span purpose="tilde">~</span>Periodic check-ins</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><span purpose="tilde">~</span>Snapshot via gather_facts or facter</div></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Open source and self-hostable</td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">MIT licensed, self-host or Fleet-host</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="❌" purpose="red-x" src="/images/icon-emoji-x-12x12@2x.png">Proprietary, cloud-only</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">Open source or open core</div></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>GitOps for endpoint configuration</td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">First-class, declarative</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="❌" purpose="red-x" src="/images/icon-emoji-x-12x12@2x.png">No native support</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">Code-native by design</div></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Built-in vulnerability detection</td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">CVE mapping, CIS benchmarks</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><span purpose="tilde">~</span>Requires Defender for Endpoint add-on</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="❌" purpose="red-x" src="/images/icon-emoji-x-12x12@2x.png">No built-in CVE detection</div></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>One console for macOS, Windows, iOS, Android</td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">All seven platforms in one place</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="checkmark" purpose="checkmark" src="/images/icon-checkmark-green-16x16@2x.png">Yes, with limits on Linux</div></td>
                  <td><div purpose="table-cell"><img alt="❌" purpose="red-x" src="/images/icon-emoji-x-12x12@2x.png">Server-focused, not endpoint UX</div></td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <div purpose="tweets-container" class="container-fluid px-md-0 pb-0 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
    <div purpose="section-heading" class="mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-3">What people are saying</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <scrollable-tweets :testimonials="testimonialsForScrollableTweets"></scrollable-tweets>
  <div purpose="bottom-gradient">

    <div purpose="page-container" class="container">
      <div purpose="bottom-cta" class="text-center">
        <h4>Linux Device Management</h4>
        <h2>Support Linux without adding complexity</h2>
        <div purpose="button-row" style="margin-top: 32px;" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center mx-auto">
          <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/whitepapers/it-leaders-guide-to-linux-device-management">Read the whitepaper</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
